concept_explanation.micrometer_core:
**Micrometer: Counter, Timer, Gauge:**

```java
import io.micrometer.core.instrument.*;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

@Service
public class PaymentMetricsService {
    private final Counter successCounter;
    private final Counter failureCounter;
    private final Timer   paymentTimer;

    PaymentMetricsService(MeterRegistry registry) {
        // COUNTER: monotonically increasing count
        successCounter = Counter.builder("payments.processed")
            .tag("status", "success")
            .tag("gateway", "visa")
            .description("Total successful payments processed")
            .register(registry);

        failureCounter = Counter.builder("payments.processed")
            .tag("status", "failure")
            .tag("gateway", "visa")
            .register(registry);

        // TIMER: duration distribution (count + sum + histogram)
        paymentTimer = Timer.builder("payments.duration")
            .tag("gateway", "visa")
            .description("Payment processing duration")
            .publishPercentiles(0.5, 0.95, 0.99)  // p50, p95, p99
            .register(registry);
    }

    public PaymentResult processPayment(PaymentRequest req) {
        return paymentTimer.record(() -> {       // RECORDS duration
            try {
                PaymentResult result = visaClient.charge(req);
                successCounter.increment();
                return result;
            } catch (Exception e) {
                failureCounter.increment();
                throw e;
            }
        });
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.gauge_and_tags:
**Gauge: track current value. Tags: query dimensions.**

```java
@Service
public class QueueMetricsService {
    private final Queue<PaymentRequest> retryQueue;

    QueueMetricsService(MeterRegistry registry,
                         Queue<PaymentRequest> queue) {
        this.retryQueue = queue;

        // GAUGE: tracks current value of something
        Gauge.builder("payments.retry.queue.size", retryQueue, Queue::size)
            .description("Number of payments waiting for retry")
            .register(registry);
        // Unlike Counter: can go UP and DOWN
        // Useful for: queue depth, connection pool usage, active requests
    }
}

// TAGS: multi-dimensional metrics — query by any tag combination:
// payments.processed{status='success', gateway='visa'}  → visa success count
// payments.processed{status='failure', gateway='visa'}  → visa failure count
// payments.processed{status='success', gateway='mastercard'} → MC success count
//
// In Prometheus:
// sum(payments_processed_total) by (status, gateway)
//   = {status='success', gateway='visa'}      → 14,523
//   = {status='failure', gateway='visa'}      → 47
//   = {status='success', gateway='mastercard'}→ 8,901
//
// PromQL: rate(payments_processed_total{status='failure'}[5m])
//   = failure rate per second, rolling 5-minute window

// @Timed annotation — shortcut for Timer:
@Timed(value = "payments.duration", description = "Payment processing time")
public PaymentResult process(PaymentRequest req) {
    return visaClient.charge(req);  // automatically timed!
}
```

